name: W3css.Responsive
comment:
Responsive Classes

W3.CSS's grid system is responsive, and the columns will re-arrange automatically depending on the screen size.


# Functions

@docs half, third, twoThird

values.name: half
values.comment:
Occupies 1/2 of the window (on medium and large screens)

    Container.div [ Responsive.half ]
      [ text "I use half of the window" ]

values.name: third
values.comment: Occupies 1/3 of the window (on medium and large screens)

values.name: twoThird
values.comment: Occupies 2/3 of the window (on medium and large screens)

name: W3css.Button

values.name: btn
values.comment:
Creates w3Css button.
A rectangular button with a shadow hover effect.
Default color is black.

    button [][ text "Button" ]
values.type: List (W3css.Types.Option msg) -> List (Html.Html msg) -> Html.Html msg

values.name: button
values.comment:
Creates w3Css button.
A rectangular button with a gray hover effect.
Default color is light-gray in W3.CSS version 3.
Default color is inherited from parent element in version 4.

    button [][ text "Button" ]
values.type: List (W3css.Types.Option msg) -> List (Html.Html msg) -> Html.Html msg

values.name: disabled
values.comment: When your `button` shall be disabled

name: W3css.Animations

values.name: animateBottom
values.comment: Slides in an element from the bottom (-300px to 0)

values.name: animateFading
values.comment: Animates an element's opacity from 0 to 1 and 1 to 0 (fades in + fade out)

values.name: animateLeft
values.comment: Slides in an element from the left (-300px to 0)

values.name: animateOpacity
values.comment: Animates an element's opacity from 0 to 1 in 1.5 seconds

values.name: animateRight
values.comment: Slides in an element from the right (-300px to 0)

values.name: animateSpin
values.comment: Spins an element 360 degrees

values.name: animateTop
values.comment: Slides in an element from the top (-300px to 0)

values.name: animateZoom
values.comment: Animates an element from 0 to 100% in size
